description.narrative:
Increased and affordable access to communications and data services in emerging markets, in particular in land-locked countries and in remote areas; 
Combining O3b's whole-sale prices (which are 50 - 80% below current levels) with open-access and competitive retail markets is expected to lead to higher quality access at sharply lower cost to the end-user in emerging markets.  It is estimated that in those markets about 50% of access costs is related with international connectivity;
It is estimated that the Project has the potential to reduce end-user broadband access costs by more than 70% in remote areas or land-locked countries of Africa.
